I see, it's a red door.

1091
01:09:51,624 --> 01:09:52,377
Welcome

1092
01:09:53,112 --> 01:09:54,285
Welcome

1093
01:09:56,022 --> 01:09:59,259
We've been waiting for you. Please come in

1094
01:09:59,290 --> 01:10:05,080
Dad, you are late.
Let him sit there.

1095
01:10:05,105 --> 01:10:06,169
What's wrong?

1096
01:10:06,228 --> 01:10:09,316
Everyone, today is the opening celebration.
Here's Kazuya's cafe.

1097
01:10:09,956 --> 01:10:11,076
Kazuyo's?

1098
01:10:13,161 --> 01:10:15,115
Dad, please hurry up.

1099
01:10:24,000 --> 01:10:27,837
He's Ryukichi Takita who work together

1100
01:10:28,075 --> 01:10:30,050
Nice to meet you.

1101
01:10:31,254 --> 01:10:33,049
Please have a seat.

1102
01:10:38,063 --> 01:10:39,935
Let me introduce you.

1103
01:10:39,960 --> 01:10:43,821
This is Mr. Sugimoto, who owns a decoration company here

1104
01:10:44,305 --> 01:10:45,831
He helped me this time.

1105
01:10:46,317 --> 01:10:47,297
I am Sugimoto

1106
01:10:47,685 --> 01:10:48,751
I am Mitsusawa .

1107
01:10:49,660 --> 01:10:50,743
So, what happened to the company?

1108
01:10:50,928 --> 01:10:51,770
I quit.

1109
01:10:51,795 --> 01:10:53,105
I didn't ask you

1110
01:10:53,410 --> 01:10:54,870
What happened to this store?

1111
01:10:55,229 --> 01:10:58,395
Um, I gave my store away to her.

1112
01:10:58,468 --> 01:10:59,340
Your store?

1113
01:10:59,823 --> 01:11:02,003
My classmate used to run a bar nearby

1114
01:11:02,390 --> 01:11:05,444
And the place I was introduced to was Mr. Aizawa's shop

1115
01:11:07,266 --> 01:11:09,185
You quit your job and
started a business like this.

1116
01:11:09,304 --> 01:11:11,247
That's great business.

1117
01:11:11,279 --> 01:11:12,599
Shut up.

1118
01:11:13,215 --> 01:11:15,185
Why did you quit your job?

1119
01:11:15,210 --> 01:11:17,940
I think it's good to be independent

1120
01:11:17,940 --> 01:11:19,886
You are still a stranger,

1121
01:11:19,949 --> 01:11:22,141
so don't be so casual about barging into my home

1122
01:11:22,214 --> 01:11:27,786
Dad, she started the business with that 500,000 yen, so isn't that okay?

1123
01:11:28,420 --> 01:11:29,543
That 500,000?

1124
01:11:30,743 --> 01:11:31,590
Yes

1125
01:11:32,560 --> 01:11:35,640
I shouldn't have shared that money

1126
01:11:35,640 --> 01:11:37,001
You are not being realistic.

1127
01:11:37,303 --> 01:11:39,215
 it doesn't matter if I'm not being realistic or not.

1128
01:11:39,254 --> 01:11:42,210
Anyway, tonight is a happy night, so let's have a toast.

1129
01:11:42,210 --> 01:11:43,141
Let's do it.

1130
01:11:43,165 --> 01:11:44,952
I don't have a cup

1131
01:11:44,977 --> 01:11:47,314
Sorry, Bring a cup for him.

1132
01:11:47,345 --> 01:11:48,532
Tatsuta.

1133
01:11:48,910 --> 01:11:50,272
You're going to betray me?

1134
01:11:50,296 --> 01:11:52,105
But that's not what I mean

1135
01:11:52,200 --> 01:11:53,530
I'm sorry.

1136
01:11:53,530 --> 01:11:56,020
I think I can drink better here than the restaurant we just went before.

1137
01:11:56,271 --> 01:11:58,860
Oh,Were you drinking somewhere?

1138
01:11:58,885 --> 01:11:59,442
No..

1139
01:11:59,568 --> 01:12:00,848
We just had some coffee.

1140
01:12:01,268 --> 01:12:02,634
Yes.

1141
01:12:03,000 --> 01:12:04,335
but that coffee was no good

1142
01:12:04,360 --> 01:12:05,983
It's expensive and very bitter.

1143
01:12:06,434 --> 01:12:08,149
You should have come here.

1144
01:12:08,385 --> 01:12:11,624
The coffee is also very delicious, isn't it? Let's have a toast

1145
01:12:11,649 --> 01:12:15,060
Yes, let's have a toast. Congratulations

1146
01:12:15,060 --> 01:12:15,822
Thank you

1147
01:12:20,193 --> 01:12:21,193
Welcome.

1148
01:12:26,160 --> 01:12:28,455
Sorry we are closed.

1149
01:12:30,127 --> 01:12:31,947
but it seems that it's opening today.

1150
01:12:39,256 --> 01:12:40,630
Good evening.

1151
01:12:40,630 --> 01:12:43,253
Sorry, we've closed the shop for the night.

1152
01:12:44,390 --> 01:12:46,511
but you have a lot of customers there.

1153
01:12:46,843 --> 01:12:48,751
They're very special people

1154
01:12:49,450 --> 01:12:52,383
I guess I deserve some special treatment too

1155
01:12:58,606 --> 01:13:01,054
I refuse. Please go home.

1156
01:13:01,078 --> 01:13:02,468
Don't say things like that

1157
01:13:02,800 --> 01:13:04,440
I want to drink beer too

1158
01:13:04,482 --> 01:13:05,248
Hey you.

1159
01:13:07,415 --> 01:13:08,700
If you want to drink beer,

1160
01:13:08,700 --> 01:13:10,509
there are standing bars around here

1161
01:13:10,613 --> 01:13:11,720
Mind your own business.

1162
01:13:11,890 --> 01:13:13,859
You are an unnecessary customer

1163
01:13:14,010 --> 01:13:16,567
Do you know what kind of guy I am?

1164
01:13:16,648 --> 01:13:17,648
No, not at all

1165
01:13:17,756 --> 01:13:21,102
I was the manager of the company where she worked.

1166
01:13:21,127 --> 01:13:24,327
Really? Then you must want to become a manager soon.

1167
01:13:24,440 --> 01:13:26,140
Okay, let me say.

1168
01:13:26,340 --> 01:13:27,314
With her...

1169
01:13:29,364 --> 01:13:32,276
If you continue talking, I will charge you.

1170
01:13:32,690 --> 01:13:35,224
it will affect to her.

1171
01:13:35,802 --> 01:13:36,621
Hey you.

1172
01:13:41,270 --> 01:13:43,011
That's enough now, go home

1173
01:13:43,960 --> 01:13:45,018
What's the matter?

1174
01:13:45,936 --> 01:13:46,431
nothing.

1175
01:13:47,495 --> 01:13:50,023
That woman and I are...

1176
01:13:50,737 --> 01:13:52,083
What's the hell?

1177
01:13:58,585 --> 01:13:59,727
Hold on.

1178
01:14:01,898 --> 01:14:02,972
Hold on.

1179
01:14:20,810 --> 01:14:25,662
I think you know the reason I left the company.

1180
01:14:35,818 --> 01:14:38,330
Congratulations Iwasaki-kun and congratulations Kiyoko-san

1181
01:14:38,880 --> 01:14:40,630
Everyone has already congratulated them.

1182
01:14:40,655 --> 01:14:42,188
I have nothing more to say

1183
01:14:42,670 --> 01:14:45,988
I'm just jealous, he's a lucky guy

1184
01:14:46,565 --> 01:14:51,525
I'll end this by confessing that I want to get married as soon as possible

1185
01:14:58,808 --> 01:15:03,936
Next, I would like to ask Shinako Mitsusawa to speech.

1186
01:15:04,390 --> 01:15:06,543
Oh, I'm in trouble.

1187
01:15:06,568 --> 01:15:07,451
Do it.

1188
01:15:09,030 --> 01:15:11,320
No problem, you're the sponsor

1189
01:15:11,320 --> 01:15:12,666
We need to speech.

1190
01:15:14,766 --> 01:15:15,233
Excuse me.

1191
01:15:16,074 --> 01:15:19,365
Before Ms. Misawa, I would like to say a few words

1192
01:15:22,651 --> 01:15:29,570
To be honest, the hardest part about
getting married was finding an apartment

1193
01:15:29,570 --> 01:15:32,340
I was renting the second floor of my brother's house

1194
01:15:32,340 --> 01:15:35,640
This Noda guy is a little strange

1195
01:15:35,640 --> 01:15:36,191
Kiyoko..

1196
01:15:36,237 --> 01:15:38,519
Don't push yourself too hard.

1197
01:15:38,556 --> 01:15:40,669
She's being looked after by her uncle

1198
01:15:41,240 --> 01:15:45,004
To rent an apartment, a deposit of 100,000 yen was required

1199
01:15:45,565 --> 01:15:49,425
In other words, Nobuko Misawa lent us the 100,000 yen

1200
01:15:49,450 --> 01:15:51,692
we needed it for our wedding

1201
01:15:57,782 --> 01:16:04,762
The 100,000 yen was something she had received
from her father's retirement pension as a wedding fund

1202
01:16:05,526 --> 01:16:09,883
We intend to pay the money back within a year

1203
01:16:10,715 --> 01:16:13,635
Please Mitsuzawa-san, please don't get married within a year

1204
01:16:13,660 --> 01:16:15,160
That's terrible! No, no,

1205
01:16:16,176 --> 01:16:18,045
no, no! I'm not saying never

1206
01:16:18,076 --> 01:16:21,737
I ask you to take responsibility for borrowing money for your wedding funds.

1207
01:16:23,390 --> 01:16:28,310
According to Hirose-kun, the two of you plan to get married someday

1208
01:16:28,310 --> 01:16:30,750
If possible, I would like you to marry after a year

1209
01:16:35,005 --> 01:16:35,758
Hold on.

1210
01:16:39,777 --> 01:16:44,150
So, thank you so much for being so happy with my little bit of help

1211
01:16:44,150 --> 01:16:46,490
I think I did a really good thing

1212
01:16:47,940 --> 01:16:53,000
But the thing about Hirose-san was a real surprise to me

1213
01:16:53,000 --> 01:16:56,660
I will now revoke it again here

1214
01:16:56,660 --> 01:17:01,637
He drinks a lot and is the best in the world at making me snort

1215
01:17:02,223 --> 01:17:06,182
As for my opponent, He's a complete failure.

1216
01:17:08,585 --> 01:17:10,378
Chairman, please make an emergency motion.

1217
01:17:10,968 --> 01:17:13,805
I would like to give special
permission to speak.

1218
01:17:13,829 --> 01:17:14,605
Thank you

1219
01:17:16,180 --> 01:17:20,150
I would like to sue her for defamation regarding her statement just now

1220
01:17:20,150 --> 01:17:22,480
In fact, she was so embarrassed

1221
01:17:22,480 --> 01:17:24,430
So She insulted to me.

1222
01:17:24,626 --> 01:17:26,755
and will not pursue a lawsuit

1223
01:17:28,222 --> 01:17:29,108
What's the hell?

1224
01:17:30,660 --> 01:17:34,167
We too will have a happy marriage like Imazeki-kun

1225
01:17:34,200 --> 01:17:35,380
Please look forward to it.

1226
01:17:41,033 --> 01:17:42,180
You shamed on me.

1227
01:17:42,253 --> 01:17:43,240


1228
01:17:43,493 --> 01:17:44,920
Can I not be angry about this too?

1229
01:17:45,560 --> 01:17:47,650
You're trying to tear me apart?

1230
01:17:47,959 --> 01:17:49,690
You're the one who tore me apart

1231
01:17:49,844 --> 01:17:51,647
I feel like killing myself I was about to kill myself

1232
01:17:51,794 --> 01:17:55,440
Suicide?
You were exaggerating a lot.

1233
01:17:55,755 --> 01:17:57,429
Let's have a meal.
I'll treat you.

1234
01:17:57,454 --> 01:17:58,755
What's the hell?

1235
01:17:58,780 --> 01:17:59,862
You're borrowing money from me anyway,

1236
01:18:00,139 --> 01:18:01,492
It's ok because 10% daily interest.

1237
01:18:01,517 --> 01:18:02,491
I will write an IOU tomorrow.

1238
01:18:02,516 --> 01:18:03,065
I can't.

1239
01:18:03,344 --> 01:18:05,740
but if you lend it to me, you'll make money

1240
01:18:06,137 --> 01:18:08,503
I get it.
You're borrowing money from me,

1241
01:18:08,528 --> 01:18:13,771
and deceiving me, marrying me, and plotting to default on your debt in the name of marriage

1242
01:18:13,796 --> 01:18:16,086
Don't say such pathetic things

1243
01:18:16,225 --> 01:18:17,695
Do I look like that bad man?

1244
01:18:17,720 --> 01:18:19,810
If I have suck an idea, I'll be much more successful.

1245
01:18:19,810 --> 01:18:23,290
Anyway, I'm going to quit being a moneylender

1246
01:18:23,328 --> 01:18:24,055
You quit?

1247
01:18:24,156 --> 01:18:25,378
I'm in trouble.

1248
01:18:25,647 --> 01:18:31,847
If you want to improve your score even a little, never borrow money from me.

1249
01:18:32,728 --> 01:18:33,861
What's the hell?

1250
01:18:34,740 --> 01:18:36,133
What a shame for you to be so considerate

1251
01:18:36,198 --> 01:18:39,265
It's proof that your heart is turning to me.

1252
01:18:41,626 --> 01:18:42,493
What's wrong?

1253
01:19:05,572 --> 01:19:06,513
Hello!

1254
01:19:06,998 --> 01:19:08,391
Oh, it's you!

1255
01:19:08,961 --> 01:19:10,967
You seem to be waiting for someone?

1256
01:19:15,690 --> 01:19:17,665
You must be waiting for Nagata-kun.

1257
01:19:21,712 --> 01:19:24,081
Could you please go to another table?

1258
01:19:24,298 --> 01:19:27,210
I get suffocated when I'm face to face with you

1259
01:19:27,246 --> 01:19:30,343
Ah, I'll leave as soon as Nagata arrives, so that's fine

1260
01:19:31,000 --> 01:19:33,625
Ah, I'll get some coffee, bring it over there.

1261
01:19:36,820 --> 01:19:40,150
There's something I want to talk to you about regarding Nagata

1262
01:19:40,150 --> 01:19:42,073
I don't want to hear any insults

1263
01:19:43,800 --> 01:19:45,472
You haven't seen him lately,right?

1264
01:19:48,690 --> 01:19:50,190
He's busy for a reason.

1265
01:19:50,910 --> 01:19:52,700
He's getting married at the end of the month.

1266
01:19:52,945 --> 01:19:54,546
He's getting married?

1267
01:19:54,684 --> 01:19:55,780
That's exactly.

1268
01:19:57,354 --> 01:19:58,194
with me for sure.

1269
01:19:58,700 --> 01:19:59,980
But it's not true

1270
01:20:00,675 --> 01:20:07,325
He's going to get married with Fumiko Kimitsu, the daughter of the president of a financial trading company.

1271
01:20:07,350 --> 01:20:08,062
You're lying.

1272
01:20:08,139 --> 01:20:13,745
I did my research and he quit his current company and became the managing director of a financial trading company.

1273
01:20:14,600 --> 01:20:19,209
It's a win-win situation because it helps my brother get promoted at his company and also helps me get promoted.

1274
01:20:19,663 --> 01:20:20,469
It's a lie

1275
01:20:20,630 --> 01:20:21,628
Who believe that?

1276
01:20:22,039 --> 01:20:23,986
Why you don't believe me?

1277
01:20:24,310 --> 01:20:28,412
I didn't run around and investigated for you. See you later

1278
01:20:38,441 --> 01:20:39,448
Did you wait long?

1279
01:20:40,840 --> 01:20:42,230
more than 40 minutes.

1280
01:20:42,381 --> 01:20:43,154
I’m sorry.

1281
01:20:43,504 --> 01:20:47,357
I'm busy at work day time and take care of my bros at night.

1282
01:20:47,926 --> 01:20:50,096
No matter how many times I call, you aren’t at home

1283
01:20:52,972 --> 01:20:53,612
Let's go out.

1284
01:21:05,479 --> 01:21:07,173
Thank you

1285
01:21:32,241 --> 01:21:36,214
Hold on.
Let's go in　for a bit

1286
01:21:38,201 --> 01:21:39,527
That's bad.

1287
01:21:41,086 --> 01:21:41,973
 Why is that?

1288
01:21:42,324 --> 01:21:44,465
I mean,we're not married yet, right?

1289
01:21:44,710 --> 01:21:46,440
You forced on me the other day

1290
01:21:46,440 --> 01:21:48,130
No, I regretted it a lot later

1291
01:21:49,092 --> 01:21:50,795
I'll confess like a man

1292
01:21:51,393 --> 01:21:53,893
Is there a reason you don't want to invite me to a hotel anymore?

1293
01:22:00,534 --> 01:22:03,651
I invited you tonight just to try it out.

1294
01:22:04,371 --> 01:22:05,442
Well, Let's go

1295
01:22:06,950 --> 01:22:09,123
I think I heard it all from Ishibe-kun

1296
01:22:09,520 --> 01:22:11,628
I'm getting married with a woman at the end of this month

1297
01:22:12,136 --> 01:22:13,612
What about our promise?

1298
01:22:13,945 --> 01:22:17,816
Hmm? Well, it's like it never happened.

1299
01:22:18,330 --> 01:22:19,970
You say that very frankly

1300
01:22:19,970 --> 01:22:21,952
No,you know

1301
01:22:22,193 --> 01:22:26,629
If you love me, you'll understand, right? For my sake,

1302
01:22:27,126 --> 01:22:28,623
Don't you think about my happiness?

1303
01:22:31,950 --> 01:22:34,170
the 500,000 yen I borrowed from you..

1304
01:22:34,170 --> 01:22:36,310
Well, I'll give it back if that happens.

1305
01:22:36,310 --> 01:22:38,270
I'll just throw that stuff away

1306
01:22:38,693 --> 01:22:39,813
Oh my god.

1307
01:22:44,118 --> 01:22:48,446
I'll pay you back the money I borrowed,
whether you throw it away or not

1308
01:22:49,020 --> 01:22:52,544
Because if I keep borrowing money for no reason, I will be hindering my career advancement.

1309
01:22:53,137 --> 01:22:54,729
You're an egoistic monster.

1310
01:22:54,980 --> 01:22:56,350
Everyone is egoistic

1311
01:22:56,350 --> 01:22:57,946
Everyone thinks they're cute

1312
01:22:58,580 --> 01:23:02,410
This time, too, is a once in a lifetime opportunity for me

1313
01:23:02,410 --> 01:23:04,040
I have to take that chance

1314
01:23:04,040 --> 01:23:07,400
Is it your chance to marry the president's daughter
and become a senior managing director?

1315
01:23:07,547 --> 01:23:08,393
Of course.

1316
01:23:09,260 --> 01:23:11,436
because as a salary man, you advance up the ladder

1317
01:23:12,150 --> 01:23:13,700
Just try acting like a normal person

1318
01:23:13,700 --> 01:23:17,460
I'll ride the train all my life and punch a time card, and that's how I'll grow old

1319
01:23:17,460 --> 01:23:19,181
Isn't your father a good example?

1320
01:23:19,206 --> 01:23:20,997
He's a great man

1321
01:23:21,022 --> 01:23:22,784
Don't look down on him.

1322
01:23:22,890 --> 01:23:23,752
Excuse me

1323
01:23:25,720 --> 01:23:28,320
Anyway, I'll give you your money back

1324
01:23:29,170 --> 01:23:31,507
Instead, One year installment payment please.

1325
01:23:31,705 --> 01:23:34,342
I will pay the interest rate be 10%.

1326
01:23:38,650 --> 01:23:40,352
Well, I'll send it to you every month

1327
01:24:49,673 --> 01:24:50,385
Hey

1328
01:24:50,410 --> 01:24:51,676
Mitsuzawa?

1329
01:24:56,937 --> 01:24:57,970
It's raining.

1330
01:25:03,710 --> 01:25:04,434
Let's go

1331
01:25:05,500 --> 01:25:06,797
You're going to catch a cold.

1332
01:25:06,834 --> 01:25:08,048
You were just watching us?

1333
01:25:08,995 --> 01:25:09,622
Yes

1334
01:25:10,547 --> 01:25:11,954
Did I looked pretty stupid?

1335
01:25:13,038 --> 01:25:13,912
Kind of.

1336
01:25:14,753 --> 01:25:16,176
You can despise me.

1337
01:25:16,794 --> 01:25:18,354
I won't.

1338
01:25:19,870 --> 01:25:20,568
Let's go.

1339
01:25:22,736 --> 01:25:23,516
Ishibe.

1340
01:25:31,543 --> 01:25:33,151
I know that, I know that,

1341
01:25:33,176 --> 01:25:34,564
Stop crying.

1342
01:25:35,930 --> 01:25:38,531
It seems that I ended up to win.

1343
01:25:48,755 --> 01:25:52,910
Come on! Strike! Good ball!

1344
01:25:53,303 --> 01:25:53,997
When did you come?

1345
01:25:54,283 --> 01:25:55,210
Just right now.

1346
01:25:55,383 --> 01:25:56,523
He's only my son.

1347
01:25:56,710 --> 01:25:57,300
I know

1348
01:25:57,619 --> 01:25:58,468
Oh, why?

1349
01:25:58,493 --> 01:26:00,230
I just felt so.
Let me play with him.

